{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488639421,"sessionID":"ses_0bfd0e5b8ffeU7MvrL6T6jXOre","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_3edda7a4c9f444c2af596df3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\necho \"=== cli-guards.cjs classifyLineageFailure body (155-210) ===\"\nsed -n '150,210p' .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs\necho \"\"\necho \"=== model_profiles GLM + MiMo blocks ===\"\nrg -n \"glm-5.2|glm5|mimo|MiMo|fallback_target\" .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json 2>/dev/null | head -30","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"=== cli-guards.cjs classifyLineageFailure body (155-210) ===\n  return number !== null && number >= 0 ? number : null;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSalvageSummary(value) {\n  if (!value || typeof value !== 'object' || Array.isArray(value)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return {\n    salvaged: readNonNegativeInteger(value.salvaged) ?? 0,\n    failed: readNonNegativeInteger(value.failed) ?? 0,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Classify a lineage failure using only bounded process and salvage signals.\n *\n * @param {Error|Object} error - Error object from a failed lineage worker.\n * @returns {{failure_class:string,retry_verdict:string,retryable:boolean,exit_code:number|null,timed_out:boolean,salvage:{salvaged:number,failed:number}|null}}\n */\nfunction classifyLineageFailure(error) {\n  const timedOut = Boolean(error && typeof error === 'object' && error.timedOut === true);\n  const exitCode = error && typeof error === 'object' ? readFiniteInteger(error.exitCode) : null;\n  const salvage = error && typeof error === 'object' ? normalizeSalvageSummary(error.salvage) : null;\n\n  let failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.EXIT;\n  if (timedOut) {\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.TIMEOUT;\n  } else if (salvage && salvage.failed > 0 && salvage.salvaged === 0) {\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.SALVAGE_MISS;\n  } else if (salvage && salvage.failed > 0) {\n    // Mixed salvage: at least one iteration was recovered but some artifact/iteration\n    // markdown was unrecoverable or a top-level artifact went missing. This is a\n    // transient artifact-recovery gap, not a fatal exit, so it should be retried rather\n    // than consumed as terminal. Without this branch a { salvaged: >0, failed: >0 }\n    // lineage fell through to EXIT (fatal) and was never retried.\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.ARTIFACT_MISS;\n  }\n\n  const retryable =\n    failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.TIMEOUT\n    || failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.SALVAGE_MISS\n    || failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.ARTIFACT_MISS;\n  return {\n    failure_class: failureClass,\n    retry_verdict: retryable ? LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.TRANSIENT : LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.FATAL,\n    retryable,\n    exit_code: exitCode,\n    timed_out: timedOut,\n    salvage,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Throw a synthetic fault when the DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT environment\n * variable is set. Used by contract tests to verify that scripts\n * handle injected DB and script-level errors correctly.\n *\n * @throws {Error} With code DB_ERROR or generic script error.\n */\nfunction maybeThrowTestFault() {\n  if (process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT === 'db') {\n\n=== model_profiles GLM + MiMo blocks ===\n3:  \"description\": \"Shared small-model profile registry for cli-opencode dispatch. Each model declares one or more executor paths with their provider + quota_pool, so the fallback engine can route across pools when one is exhausted. Active small-model rotation: DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code (Kimi For Coding plan via provider `kimi-for-coding`), MiniMax-M3 (default via the MiniMax Token Plan provider `minimax-coding-plan`; pay-per-token Direct API via provider `minimax`), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via the Xiaomi Token Plan Europe provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` or Xiaomi Direct API provider `xiaomi`), GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan via provider `zai-coding-plan`). Optional unverified separate-pool stub: Claude Haiku.\",\n20:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n71:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n114:          \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 6 samples/cell, throttled serial real kimi-for-coding/k2p7 dispatches. (The 4th fixture hard-roman-to-int was excluded - its run stalled under orchestration churn; the 3-fixture result is conclusive.) Unlike the saturated run 006, correctness SEPARATED here. Per-framework correctness (n=18): tidd-ec 1.0 = race 1.0 = costar 1.0 (perfect tier) > cidi 0.996 > rcaf 0.992. Trust verdict: TIE on correctness (the 3 perfect frameworks cannot be statistically separated, top-pair margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). The actionable signal: rcaf (the former convention default) is objectively the WEAKEST - it produced strict-validator code that missed adversarial cases - so it is retired/avoided for this model. Among the perfect tier, costar is primary for cross-evidence robustness (also MiMo's empirical winner, benchmark 004; favored by run 006's judge); tidd-ec is the most token-efficient (25 vs costar 70 median words) and is the fallback. This objectively refutes run 006's subjective gpt-5.5 judge, which had wrongly ranked rcaf/race highest.\",\n143:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n190:      \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n200:          \"notes\": \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) via opencode provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (credential 'Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)'). Live slug xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro (confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13, 2026-06-01); verify the full live list with 'opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams'. Omit --agent (warns + falls back on 1.15.13). Manual direct-provider reroute uses xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined. Context window 1,000,000 tokens (released 2026-04-22). OpenAI-compatible endpoint https://token-plan-ams.xiaomimimo.com/v1; opencode cost shows 0/0 (Token-Plan subscription). --variant maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) in opencode settings — always dispatch with --variant high (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13). Best prompt framework (benchmark 004, 10/10 real runs): COSTAR or RACE + lean pre-planning — frame for format/brevity, not guardrails; TIDD-EC/dense ranked last; avoid CIDI (intermittent tool-only file-writes).\"\n204:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n207:        \"model_slug\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n214:        \"notes\": \"Live slug `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13 (2026-06-01). default_variant high: `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) and `--variant high` is confirmed accepted — always dispatch with it. agent_policy omit-general: `--agent` warns and falls back on 1.15.13. format_mode json: OpenAI-compatible endpoint; dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized envelope. Manual direct-provider reroutes use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined.\",\n225:        \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n231:        \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents — spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n247:          \"sample\": \"10/10 real MiMo-V2.5-Pro runs at --variant high\",\n250:        \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md\",\n255:      \"id\": \"glm-5.2\",\n265:          \"notes\": \"Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (subscription) via opencode provider `zai-coding-plan` (auth credential 'Z.AI Coding Plan'). Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`; confirmed present via `opencode models zai-coding-plan` 2026-06-28 → glm-4.5-air/glm-4.7/glm-5-turbo/glm-5.1/glm-5.2/glm-5v-turbo. Flagship long-horizon coding model (supersedes the gateway-only glm-5.1 removed in cli-opencode v1.3.15.0). context_length 1,000,000 / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs — opencode `models` did not expose limits, re-verify. Omit `--agent` at top level. GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it. Thinking is on by default and the Coding Plan endpoint preserves thinking. Re-verify the live slug before automation — Z.AI ids drift (provider also serves glm-4.7 / glm-5.1 / glm-5-turbo).\"\n269:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n272:        \"model_slug\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n283:        \"vision\": \"native vision-to-code; image input via the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 image_url block at https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions) — opencode `--file` does NOT deliver images to this provider per upstream #20802; confirmed live 2026-06-28; see references/models/glm-5.2.md §7\",\n284:        \"notes\": \"Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` confirmed present 2026-06-28 (`opencode models zai-coding-plan`). agent_policy omit-general: do not pass `--agent` at the top level. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high + variant_status accepted-unverified: GLM's native `reasoning_effort` has high/max, but whether opencode `--variant high/max` forwards to it is not confirmed — smoke-test, do not depend on it. Subscription billing: confirm dispatch cost via smoke test. GLM dispatch quirks (Z.AI docs): thinking on by default + preserved thinking on the Coding Plan endpoint; function-calling `tool_choice` only `auto`; streaming tool calls need `tool_stream=true`. Re-verify slug before dispatch (Z.AI ids drift).\"\n311:          \"benchmark\": \"008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework\",\n314:          \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 3 samples/cell, real zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 dispatches graded by the deterministic hidden-test oracle (grader noop, no LLM-judge bias). Run status SEPARABLE: per-framework correctness costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976 (the ONLY sub-perfect framework; also worst format adherence 0.889). Trust verdict TIE on correctness among the perfect tier (top-pair costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). costar is primary as best-of-tied: perfect correctness + tersest output (13 median words vs tidd-ec 38, cidi/race 94) + cross-model corroboration (also the empirical winner for kimi benchmark 007 and mimo benchmark 004). tidd-ec fallback (perfect, 2nd-tersest). rcaf avoided (only correctness misses + worst format). NOTE: CRAFT (the phase-1 doc-guided default) is NOT in the harness framework registry [rcaf,race,cidi,tidd-ec,costar] so it could not be benchmarked; the empirical winner among the 5 supported frameworks replaces it. 1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, excluded from scoring).\",\n317:        \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n336:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n","metadata":{"output":"=== cli-guards.cjs classifyLineageFailure body (155-210) ===\n  return number !== null && number >= 0 ? number : null;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSalvageSummary(value) {\n  if (!value || typeof value !== 'object' || Array.isArray(value)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return {\n    salvaged: readNonNegativeInteger(value.salvaged) ?? 0,\n    failed: readNonNegativeInteger(value.failed) ?? 0,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Classify a lineage failure using only bounded process and salvage signals.\n *\n * @param {Error|Object} error - Error object from a failed lineage worker.\n * @returns {{failure_class:string,retry_verdict:string,retryable:boolean,exit_code:number|null,timed_out:boolean,salvage:{salvaged:number,failed:number}|null}}\n */\nfunction classifyLineageFailure(error) {\n  const timedOut = Boolean(error && typeof error === 'object' && error.timedOut === true);\n  const exitCode = error && typeof error === 'object' ? readFiniteInteger(error.exitCode) : null;\n  const salvage = error && typeof error === 'object' ? normalizeSalvageSummary(error.salvage) : null;\n\n  let failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.EXIT;\n  if (timedOut) {\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.TIMEOUT;\n  } else if (salvage && salvage.failed > 0 && salvage.salvaged === 0) {\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.SALVAGE_MISS;\n  } else if (salvage && salvage.failed > 0) {\n    // Mixed salvage: at least one iteration was recovered but some artifact/iteration\n    // markdown was unrecoverable or a top-level artifact went missing. This is a\n    // transient artifact-recovery gap, not a fatal exit, so it should be retried rather\n    // than consumed as terminal. Without this branch a { salvaged: >0, failed: >0 }\n    // lineage fell through to EXIT (fatal) and was never retried.\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.ARTIFACT_MISS;\n  }\n\n  const retryable =\n    failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.TIMEOUT\n    || failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.SALVAGE_MISS\n    || failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.ARTIFACT_MISS;\n  return {\n    failure_class: failureClass,\n    retry_verdict: retryable ? LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.TRANSIENT : LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.FATAL,\n    retryable,\n    exit_code: exitCode,\n    timed_out: timedOut,\n    salvage,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Throw a synthetic fault when the DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT environment\n * variable is set. Used by contract tests to verify that scripts\n * handle injected DB and script-level errors correctly.\n *\n * @throws {Error} With code DB_ERROR or generic script error.\n */\nfunction maybeThrowTestFault() {\n  if (process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT === 'db') {\n\n=== model_profiles GLM + MiMo blocks ===\n3:  \"description\": \"Shared small-model profile registry for cli-opencode dispatch. Each model declares one or more executor paths with their provider + quota_pool, so the fallback engine can route across pools when one is exhausted. Active small-model rotation: DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code (Kimi For Coding plan via provider `kimi-for-coding`), MiniMax-M3 (default via the MiniMax Token Plan provider `minimax-coding-plan`; pay-per-token Direct API via provider `minimax`), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via the Xiaomi Token Plan Europe provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` or Xiaomi Direct API provider `xiaomi`), GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan via provider `zai-coding-plan`). Optional unverified separate-pool stub: Claude Haiku.\",\n20:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n71:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n114:          \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 6 samples/cell, throttled serial real kimi-for-coding/k2p7 dispatches. (The 4th fixture hard-roman-to-int was excluded - its run stalled under orchestration churn; the 3-fixture result is conclusive.) Unlike the saturated run 006, correctness SEPARATED here. Per-framework correctness (n=18): tidd-ec 1.0 = race 1.0 = costar 1.0 (perfect tier) > cidi 0.996 > rcaf 0.992. Trust verdict: TIE on correctness (the 3 perfect frameworks cannot be statistically separated, top-pair margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). The actionable signal: rcaf (the former convention default) is objectively the WEAKEST - it produced strict-validator code that missed adversarial cases - so it is retired/avoided for this model. Among the perfect tier, costar is primary for cross-evidence robustness (also MiMo's empirical winner, benchmark 004; favored by run 006's judge); tidd-ec is the most token-efficient (25 vs costar 70 median words) and is the fallback. This objectively refutes run 006's subjective gpt-5.5 judge, which had wrongly ranked rcaf/race highest.\",\n143:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n190:      \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n200:          \"notes\": \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) via opencode provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (credential 'Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)'). Live slug xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro (confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13, 2026-06-01); verify the full live list with 'opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams'. Omit --agent (warns + falls back on 1.15.13). Manual direct-provider reroute uses xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined. Context window 1,000,000 tokens (released 2026-04-22). OpenAI-compatible endpoint https://token-plan-ams.xiaomimimo.com/v1; opencode cost shows 0/0 (Token-Plan subscription). --variant maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) in opencode settings — always dispatch with --variant high (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13). Best prompt framework (benchmark 004, 10/10 real runs): COSTAR or RACE + lean pre-planning — frame for format/brevity, not guardrails; TIDD-EC/dense ranked last; avoid CIDI (intermittent tool-only file-writes).\"\n204:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n207:        \"model_slug\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n214:        \"notes\": \"Live slug `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13 (2026-06-01). default_variant high: `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) and `--variant high` is confirmed accepted — always dispatch with it. agent_policy omit-general: `--agent` warns and falls back on 1.15.13. format_mode json: OpenAI-compatible endpoint; dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized envelope. Manual direct-provider reroutes use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined.\",\n225:        \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n231:        \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents — spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n247:          \"sample\": \"10/10 real MiMo-V2.5-Pro runs at --variant high\",\n250:        \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md\",\n255:      \"id\": \"glm-5.2\",\n265:          \"notes\": \"Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (subscription) via opencode provider `zai-coding-plan` (auth credential 'Z.AI Coding Plan'). Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`; confirmed present via `opencode models zai-coding-plan` 2026-06-28 → glm-4.5-air/glm-4.7/glm-5-turbo/glm-5.1/glm-5.2/glm-5v-turbo. Flagship long-horizon coding model (supersedes the gateway-only glm-5.1 removed in cli-opencode v1.3.15.0). context_length 1,000,000 / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs — opencode `models` did not expose limits, re-verify. Omit `--agent` at top level. GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it. Thinking is on by default and the Coding Plan endpoint preserves thinking. Re-verify the live slug before automation — Z.AI ids drift (provider also serves glm-4.7 / glm-5.1 / glm-5-turbo).\"\n269:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n272:        \"model_slug\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n283:        \"vision\": \"native vision-to-code; image input via the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 image_url block at https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions) — opencode `--file` does NOT deliver images to this provider per upstream #20802; confirmed live 2026-06-28; see references/models/glm-5.2.md §7\",\n284:        \"notes\": \"Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` confirmed present 2026-06-28 (`opencode models zai-coding-plan`). agent_policy omit-general: do not pass `--agent` at the top level. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high + variant_status accepted-unverified: GLM's native `reasoning_effort` has high/max, but whether opencode `--variant high/max` forwards to it is not confirmed — smoke-test, do not depend on it. Subscription billing: confirm dispatch cost via smoke test. GLM dispatch quirks (Z.AI docs): thinking on by default + preserved thinking on the Coding Plan endpoint; function-calling `tool_choice` only `auto`; streaming tool calls need `tool_stream=true`. Re-verify slug before dispatch (Z.AI ids drift).\"\n311:          \"benchmark\": \"008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework\",\n314:          \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 3 samples/cell, real zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 dispatches graded by the deterministic hidden-test oracle (grader noop, no LLM-judge bias). Run status SEPARABLE: per-framework correctness costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976 (the ONLY sub-perfect framework; also worst format adherence 0.889). Trust verdict TIE on correctness among the perfect tier (top-pair costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). costar is primary as best-of-tied: perfect correctness + tersest output (13 median words vs tidd-ec 38, cidi/race 94) + cross-model corroboration (also the empirical winner for kimi benchmark 007 and mimo benchmark 004). tidd-ec fallback (perfect, 2nd-tersest). rcaf avoided (only correctness misses + worst format). NOTE: CRAFT (the phase-1 doc-guided default) is NOT in the harness framework registry [rcaf,race,cidi,tidd-ec,costar] so it could not be benchmarked; the empirical winner among the 5 supported frameworks replaces it. 1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, excluded from scoring).\",\n317:        \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n336:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\necho \"=== cli-guards.cjs classifyLineageFailure body (155-210) ===\"\nsed -n '150,210p' .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs\necho \"\"\necho \"=== model_profiles GLM + MiMo blocks ===\"\nrg -n \"glm-5.2|glm5|mimo|MiMo|fallback_target\" .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json 2>/dev/null | head -30","time":{"start":1783488639416,"end":1783488639419}},"id":"prt_f4034f1a6001SwbGllu87dFUsv","sessionID":"ses_0bfd0e5b8ffeU7MvrL6T6jXOre","messageID":"msg_f4034c9ae001irjcnwzp1Txsmu"}}
